[[File:Frankfurt Am Main-Stadtansicht von der Deutschherrnbruecke am fruehen Abend-20110808.jpg|thumb|Skyline of Mainhattan at night]]
'''Mainhattan''' is the [[central business district]] of [[Frankfurt]] in [[Germany]]. The word is a [[portmanteau]] of [[Main (river)|Main]], the river on which Frankfurt lies, and [[Manhattan]], a reference to the inner city area's visually impressive [[Tower block|high rises]] and [[skyscraper]]s. Together with [[St. Paul's Church, Frankfurt am Main|St. Paul's Church]], these buildings form the skyline of the city. The first tall buildings were built in the 1960s. Banks and other financial institutions settled there, which resulted in the district also being referred to as "Bankfurt" (''Bankford''). Originally, both expressions were sometimes used derisively, but the [[connotation]] has changed to a purely positive one.<ref>[[Der Spiegel]]: [http://www.spiegel.de/reise/staedte/mainhattan-frankfurt-feiert-seine-wolkenkratzer-a-481941.html  Mainhattan: Frankfurt feiert seine Wolkenkratzer]. Retrieved 25 June 2016.</ref><ref>[https://www.standard.co.uk/business/an-expanding-europe-welcomes-mainhattan-10250008.html Business. An expanding Europe welcomes 'Mainhattan']. Retrieved 25 June 2016</ref> The seat of the [[European Central Bank]] is located in Mainhattan. The [[Commerzbank Tower]] was the [[List of tallest buildings in Europe|tallest building in the European Union]] until [[the Shard]] in London was built. After the [[United Kingdom withdrawal from the European Union|United Kingdom voted to withdraw from the European Union]], plans were made for several financial institutions to move from the [[City of London]] to Mainhattan.<ref>[http://www.businessinsider.de/banker-ziehen-bei-brexit-nach-frankfurt-2016-6 Warum die Londoner Banker bei einem „Brexit“ nach Frankfurt übersiedeln werden]. Retrieved 25 June 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.n-tv.de/wirtschaft/Brexit-wuerde-Frankfurt-Schub-verleihen-article16896916.html Kurzfristiger positiver Effekt"Brexit würde Frankfurt Schub verleihen"]. Retrieved 25 June 2016.</ref><ref>[http://de.reuters.com/article/brexit-frankfurt-idDEKCN0Z110Z Analyse-Wer hat Angst vorm Brexit? Frankfurt nicht!]. Retrieved 25 June 2016</ref>

