=== Business analysis ===

[[Business analysis]] &ndash; set of tasks, knowledge, and techniques required to identify business needs and determine solutions to business problems. Solutions often include a systems development component, but may also consist of process improvement or organizational change. 
** [[Competitor analysis]]

=== Goal setting ===

[[Goal setting]] &ndash; involves establishing specific, measurable and time targeted objectives
* [[Goal]] &ndash; or objective consists of a projected state of affairs which a person or a system plans or intends to achieve or bring about — a personal or organizational desired end-point in some sort of assumed development. Many people endeavor to reach goals within a finite time by setting deadlines
** Examples of business objectives
*** [[Competitive advantage]] &ndash; 
**** [[Sustainable competitive advantage]]

=== Planning ===

[[Planning]] &ndash; in organizations and public policy is both the organizational process of creating and maintaining a plan; and the psychological process of thinking about the activities required to create a desired goal on some scale. 
* [[Scheduling]] &ndash; 
