{{Infobox person | name = Peter Alfond | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date|1952|5|17}} | birth_place = [[Waterville, Maine]], U.S. | birth_name = | death_date = {{death date and age|2017|7|10|1952|5|17}} | death_place = [[West Palm Beach, Florida]], U.S. | death_cause = Complications from [[malaria]] | occupation = Investor, philanthropist | known_for = | spouse = {{marriage|Karen Benson|1976|1992|end=divorced}} | children = Rebekah Alfond, Sarah Alfond, Kyle Alfond, Deborah Alfond | parents = {{ubl|Dorothy Levine Alfond|[[Harold Alfond]]}} | family = {{ubl|[[Susan Alfond]] (sister)|[[Bill Alfond]] (brother)|[[Ted Alfond]] (brother)}} }}
'''Peter Alfond''' (May 17, 1952 – July 10, 2017) was an American millionaire, investor, and philanthropist.
==Biography== Peter Alfond was born to a [[American Jews|Jewish]] family, the son of Dorothy (née Levine) and businessman-philanthropist [[Harold Alfond]].<ref name=HaroldObit>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/17/business/17alfond.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |title=Harold Alfond, Donor and Shoe Factory Owner, Dies at 93 |first=Richard |last=Pérez-Peña |authorlink=Richard Pérez-Peña |date=November 17, 2007}}</ref><ref name=Scrapbook>[http://mainejews.org/TEXT/Colby/BibbyLevineAlfondScrapbook.pdf Colby College Digital Commons: "Bibby Levine Alfond Scrapbook"] January 1, 2011</ref><ref>Silbiger, Steve [https://books.google.com/books?id=2CAGE9yJcm8C&pg=silverman#v=onepage&q=werner&f=false The Jewish Phenomenon: Seven Keys to the Enduring Wealth of a People], p. 89</ref>
Harold Alfond founded the Dexter Shoe Company in 1958 and sold it in 1995 for $433 million of [[Berkshire Hathaway]] stock.<ref name=HaroldObit/>
==Personal life== Alfond was married to Karen Benson, they met at Rollins College in Winterpark, Florida and had four children: Rebekah, Kyle, Sarah, and Deborah.<ref name=Rollins>{{cite web |url=http://lib.rollins.edu/olin/oldsite/archives/golden/alfond.htm |website=[[Rollins College]] |title=Harold Alfond (1914–2007): Business Leader and Strong Supporter of the Rollins Sports Program|access-date=July 11, 2017}}</ref><ref name=ForbesBillionaires>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/peter-alfond/?list=billionaires|title=The World's Billionaires - Peter Alfond|magazine=[[Forbes]]|date=July 2017|issn=0015-6914}}</ref>
==Death== Peter Alfond died on July 10, 2017 of complications from [[malaria]], which he had contracted on a trip to Africa. He was 65 years old.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.centralmaine.com/2017/07/11/philanthropist-peter-g-alfond-dies|title=Philanthropist Peter G. Alfond, originally from Waterville, dies of malaria|first=Amy|last=Calder|newspaper=[[Kennebec Journal]]|date=July 11, 2017}}</ref>
