{{SLA|Ireland|16|(14)|2000|The statutory minimum age is 16, except for those who have completed less than three years of secondary education, for whom it is 18.<ref name="irelandYouthGeneral">{{cite web |url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/birth_family_relationships/children_s_rights_and_policy/children_and_rights_in_ireland.html|title=Children and rights in Ireland|date=3 April 2013|work=Citizens Information|publisher=Citizens Information Board|accessdate=6 January 2014|location=Ireland}}</ref><ref name="irelandYouthSchool">
* {{cite web |url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/education/primary_and_post_primary_education/attendance_and_discipline_in_schools/school_attendance.html |title=School attendance |date=2 January 2014 |work=Citizens Information |publisher=Citizens Information Board |accessdate=6 January 2014 |location=Ireland}}
* {{cite web |url=http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/2000/en/act/pub/0022/index.html|title=Education (Welfare) Act, 2000|work=[[Irish Statute Book]]|nopp=Y|page=§§2, 17|accessdate=6 January 2014}}</ref> The minimum working ages are: 14 during school holidays; 15 during term time; 16 for working up to 40 hours per week and 8 hours per day; 18 for working with no age-based restrictions.<ref name="irelandYouthGeneral"/><ref name="irelandYouthWork"/> Employees under 18 must be registered.<ref name="irelandYouthWork">
* {{cite web |url=http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/employment/starting_work_and_changing_job/young_people_at_work/hours_of_work_for_young_people.html|title=Hours of work for young people |work=Citizens Information|publisher=Citizens Information Board|accessdate=6 January 2014|location=Ireland }}
* {{cite web|url=http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/1996/en/act/pub/0016/index.html |title=Protection of Young Persons (Employment) Act, 1996 |work=[[Irish Statute Book]] |accessdate=6 January 2014}}</ref> Exemptions may be specified by the [[Minister for Jobs, Enterprise and Innovation|Minister for Jobs]]; this has been done for close relatives.<ref name="irelandYouthWork"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/1997/en/si/0002.html|title=S.I. No. 2/1997 - Protection of Young Persons (Employment of Close Relatives) Regulations, 1997.|work=[[Irish Statute Book]]|accessdate=6 January 2014}}</ref>}}
